  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nI'm trying to deploy besu in a \"prod\" environment on Azure Kubernetes, from this repository : \r\nhttps://github.com/ConsenSys/quorum-kubernetes\r\n\r\nAll pods are running, but since a few days, I am unable to connect Metamask to my private network. Here are the error logs I'm experiencing:\r\n\r\nOn Metamask:\r\n\r\n![Metamask Connection](https://github.com/YounesBM/logs-quorum/blob/main/Metamask%20network.JPG?raw=true)\r\n\r\nOn my private network :\r\n    \r\n`kubectl logs besu-node-member-1-0 -c member-1-besu --namespace besu`\r\n\r\n![Member-1 logs](https://github.com/YounesBM/logs-quorum/blob/main/Metamask.JPG?raw=true)\r\n\r\n\r\nI have created a repository to reproduce the bug in question:\r\nhttps://github.com/YounesBM/besu-metamask-issue\r\n\r\nDo you have any idea how to fix this error?\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\nYounes",
